-# coding: utf-8
#get_metadata

  .subtitle get_metadata

  .helptext

    .comment retrieve a metadata record

    %h3 arguments:

    %table
      %thead
        %tr
          %td parameter name
          %td default value
          %td description
      %tbody
        %tr
          %td.parameter pid
          %td
          %td the PID of the object for which to retrieve the metadata records
        %tr
          %td.parameter mid
          %td
          %td the MID of the metadata record

    %br

    %p
      At least one of the <code>pid</code> and <code>mid</code> parameters is required. If both are present only the
      <code>mid</code> will be used.

    %h3 The result XML

    %p
      The Resolver will return an XML document containing the metadata details. The root element is <code>result</code>
      and it repeats the supplied parameters in its attributes.

    %p
      For each descriptive metadata record a <code>metadata</code> sub-element is added with the following
      attributes:
      %ul
        %li <code>mid</code>: the MID of the metadata record.
        %li <code>type</code>: the type of the metadata record (typically '<code>dc</code>' for Dublin Core)
      The content of the element is the descriptive metadata itself with the first line removed (the '<code><?xml ...></code>' line).
